---

<Layout>
  <div class="container my-4">
    <div class="row justify-content-center">
      <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-10">
        <a href="/courses/foce/" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-light mb-3">
          <i class="si-arrow-left"></i> Back
        </a>

        <h1>Activity 1.9: Boolean Logic</h1>
        <Divider variant="8" classes="mb-5" />

        <!-- Launch / Concept -->
        <section id="launch">
          <Presentation>
            <section>
              <h2>Activity 1.9</h2>
              <h3 class="text-sn-theme">Boolean Logic</h3>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>Key Concepts</h2>
              <p>Booleans</p>
              <p>Comparison Operators</p>
              <p>Logical Operators</p>
            </section>

            <section data-auto-animate>
              <h2>Booleans</h2>
              <p>
                A <b class="text-sn-theme">boolean</b> is a value that's
                either <CodeSnippet code="True" lang="python" theme="material-theme-ocean" inline /> or <CodeSnippet code="False" lang="python" theme="material-theme-ocean" inline /> &mdash; nothing else.
              </p>
              <Code code={Figure1} frame="code" lang="python" showLineNumbers={false} />
            </section>

            <section data-auto-animate data-auto-animate-restart>
              <h2>Comparison Operators</h2>
              <p>Comparing two values always produces a boolean.</p>
              <Code code={Figure2} frame="code" lang="python" showLineNumbers={false} />
            </section>

            <section data-auto-animate>
              <h2>Comparison Operators</h2>
              <ul>
                <li class="fragment"><CodeSnippet code="==" lang="python" theme="material-theme-ocean" inline /> Equal to</li>
                <li class="fragment"><CodeSnippet code="!=" lang="python" theme="material-theme-ocean" inline /> Not equal to</li>
                <li class="fragment"><CodeSnippet code=">" lang="python" theme="material-theme-ocean" inline /> Greater than</li>
                <li class="fragment"><CodeSnippet code="<" lang="python" theme="material-theme-ocean" inline /> Less than</li>
                <li class="fragment"><CodeSnippet code=">=" lang="python" theme="material-theme-ocean" inline /> Greater than or equal to</li>
                <li class="fragment"><CodeSnippet code="<=" lang="python" theme="material-theme-ocean" inline /> Less than or equal to</li>
              </ul>
            </section>

            <section data-auto-animate data-auto-animate-restart>
              <h2>Logical Operators</h2>
              <p>
                Logical operators combine booleans together. Python spells
                these out as words, not symbols.
              </p>
              <ul>
                <li class="fragment"><CodeSnippet code="and" lang="python" theme="material-theme-ocean" inline /> &mdash; true only if both sides are true</li>
                <li class="fragment"><CodeSnippet code="or" lang="python" theme="material-theme-ocean" inline /> &mdash; true if either side is true</li>
                <li class="fragment"><CodeSnippet code="not" lang="python" theme="material-theme-ocean" inline /> &mdash; flips a boolean to its opposite</li>
              </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>Today's Objectives</h2>
              <ul>
                <li>Writing boolean expressions with comparison operators</li>
                <li>Combining booleans with <code>and</code>, <code>or</code>, and <code>not</code></li>
              </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>Key Terms</h2>
              <div class="text-start">
                <dl>
                  <dt>Boolean</dt>
                  <dd>A value that is either <code>True</code> or <code>False</code>.</dd>
                  <dt>Comparison Operator</dt>
                  <dd>An operator like <code>==</code> or <code>&gt;=</code> that compares two values and produces a boolean.</dd>
                  <dt>Logical Operator</dt>
                  <dd><code>and</code>, <code>or</code>, and <code>not</code> &mdash; combine or invert booleans.</dd>
                </dl>
              </div>
            </section>
          </Presentation>
        </section>

        <Divider variant="8" classes="my-5" />

        <!-- Build -->
        <section id="build">
          <h2>Build</h2>

          <p>
            Create a new Python script named <b class="text-sn-theme">1-9-boolean-logic.py</b>.
          </p>

          <hr class="my-4" />

          <h3>Task 1: Boolean Expressions</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Declare the variables shown, then write four boolean expressions comparing them.</li>
          </ul>

          <Code code={Task1} frame="code" lang="python" title="1-9-boolean-logic.py" mark="9-12" />

          <hr class="my-4" />

          <h3>Task 2: Name Checks</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Print the results of the name-related boolean expressions.</li>
          </ul>

          <Code code={Task2} frame="code" lang="python" title="1-9-boolean-logic.py" mark="14-17" ins="14-18" />

          <hr class="my-4" />

          <h3>Task 3: Age-Related Checks</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Print whether the person can drive, rent a car, and get a senior discount.</li>
          </ul>

          <Code code={Task3} frame="code" lang="python" title="1-9-boolean-logic.py" mark="21-23" ins="20-25" />

          <hr class="my-4" />

          <h3>Task 4: Bank Account Checks</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Print whether the person can afford the car, and whether their balance is positive.</li>
          </ul>

          <Code code={Task4} frame="code" lang="python" title="1-9-boolean-logic.py" mark="28-29" ins="27-31" />

          <hr class="my-4" />

          <h3>Task 5: Boolean Checks</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Print the teacher/millionaire booleans directly, then use <code>not</code> to flip one.</li>
          </ul>

          <Code code={Task5} frame="code" lang="python" title="1-9-boolean-logic.py" mark="34-37" ins="33-38" />

          <hr class="my-4" />

          <h3>Task 6: Logical Operator Examples</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Combine <code>can_drive</code> and <code>can_buy_car</code> with both <code>and</code> and <code>or</code>.</li>
          </ul>

          <Code code={Task6} frame="code" lang="python" title="1-9-boolean-logic.py" mark="41,43" ins="40-44" />
        </section>

        <Divider variant="8" classes="my-5" />

        <!-- Checkpoint -->
        <section id="checkpoint">
          <h2>Checkpoint</h2>

          <p>Verify your program works correctly.</p>

          <Code
            code={SampleOutput}
            frame="terminal"
            lang="txt"
            showLineNumbers={false}
            title="Example Output"
          />
        </section>

        <Divider variant="8" classes="my-5" />

        <!-- Reflection -->
        <section id="reflection">
          <h2>Reflection</h2>

          <p>Answer the following questions before submitting your work.</p>

          <ol>
            <li>What are the only two values a boolean can hold?</li>
            <li>What's the difference between <code>and</code> and <code>or</code>?</li>
            <li>If <code>can_drive</code> is <code>True</code> and <code>can_buy_car</code> is <code>False</code>, what does <code>not can_buy_car</code> evaluate to?</li>
          </ol>
        </section>

        <Divider variant="8" classes="my-5" />

        <!-- Submit -->
        <section id="submit">
          <h2>Submit</h2>

          <p>Submit the required files to the appropriate dropbox.</p>

          <h1
            class="text-center mt-5 text-sn-theme border border-primary slow-flash"
          >
            Activity Complete
          </h1>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
